{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771863369,"nonce":"9nqM3Q0sYbUmsMcfX80tMVdtX58=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87tKrvD","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/252","origin":"github"},"title":"Recover intent behind scripts and Makefile targets for interface redesign","message":"## Problem\n\nThe workspace has 42 scripts in `.agent/scripts/` and 19 Makefile targets. Many were added to solve specific problems, but the intents behind them aren't documented. Some scripts overlap, some may be dead, and the collection as a whole is difficult to navigate.\n\nBefore redesigning the interface, we need to understand what purposes the current tools serve — otherwise we risk losing valuable functionality or recreating problems that were already solved.\n\n## Approach\n\nFor each script and Makefile target:\n1. What problem does it solve? (the intent)\n2. Is that problem still relevant?\n3. Are multiple scripts serving the same intent?\n\nGroup by intent, not by implementation. The output is a map from intents to current implementations, which becomes the input for redesigning a simpler set of tools.\n\nThis is not a standalone inventory exercise — it's the foundation for the interface redesign work tracked under #249. Intents that represent design decisions should be captured as ADRs (#251).\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- Actually redesigning the scripts or Makefile (that's a follow-up)\n- Evaluating replacement tools like `just` (that decision comes later, informed by this)\n\nParent tracking issue: #249\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}